text:
A secondary correction, it‚Äôs better to remove the quotation marks around she, since quotations are usually meant to refer to
1) A product, such as the name of a song, a game, a book, etc.
2) A part of what someone has said(i.e., quoting someone).
3) A specific word that isn‚Äôt a noun, but is treated as one in that scenario(usually when referring to the word itself instead of its definition).
or 4) A word that isn‚Äôt actually being used for its proper meaning.

So when r k said that you should replace ‚ÄúI‚Äù with ‚Äúshe,‚Äù he meant that you should place ‚Äúshe‚Äù without the quotation marks, as he was only using the quotations to show that he is referring to the word itself.
